#ad21+ #Dobel50SilverOak I recently spent some time in Napa Valley with my friends at @dobeltequila & @silveroakcellars to celebrate the launch of their latest partnership, the Dobel 50 Silver Oak edition. 
 
For its reveal hosted at the Silver Oak winery, Maestro Dobel founder and 11th-generation tequila maker, Juan Dobel hosted me and a room full of distinguished guests for a three-course tasting and it did not disappoint. 
 
The bottle for the partnership itself is design gold. Truly, I have never seen anything like it. The taste is what makes it irreplaceable. The Dobel 50 Silver Oak edition is exceptional and a true reflection of a masterful partnership tying in the signatures of both Silver Oak and Maestro Dobel. Whilst Dobel tequila is famous for its smoothness and complexities, the weight of the Silver Oak Cabernet Sauvignon barrels is present alongside notes of punchy fruit for a more sophisticated tasting experience.

What is Tony Parker envisioning for his future? “Taking stock and gearing up for a strong year – literally! ” he tells BOND OFFICIAL. After an extensive career that has earned Parker four NBA championship titles and numerous accolades, the former San Antonio @spurs star currently has transitioned into a succeeding career as an investor. His current portfolio includes ventures such as LDLC ASVEL, the Tony Parker Adéquat Academy, and even a ski resort. 

About a year ago, Parker teamed up with the owner of Cos d’Estournel, Michel Reybier to launch brands, @lamascaronne, and @champagnejeeper. 

#TonyParker wears @bmcstudio, @nililotan, @ferragamo, @hermes and @jacquesmariemage. 

See the full editorial now on www.bondofficial.com/living. #WORLDOFBOND #BONDIRL #BONDSOCIAL #BONDOFFICIAL

In our latest story with @_tonyparker09,  he touches on the distinguishing qualities between his basketball career and transitioning into wine. “My game was always about speed, which served me well on the court. ” says the entrepreneur. “off the court, I’ve come to rely on some of the other skills that Coach Pop honed in me: discipline, and motivation too, without a doubt. But, also, self-belief.”

The venture with @lamascaronne and @champagnejeeper, two of his first wines with Michel Reybier feel like the ideal way to jumpstart his winemaking career, which is also gearing up to be a very busy one this year. “I always say, I’m in this game for the long haul,” he says. “With Michael Reybier, I get to learn from someone with more than twenty years of experience making some of the most incredible Bordeaux at Cos d’Estournel––who’s now putting all that know-how into making some of the most incredible Provence rosé and Champagne with La Mascaronne and Jeeper. So, I want to keep learning as much as I can.”

Last week I arrived in Florence, Italy, for #PittiUomo.

Before the trip, I had only attended summer shows, so I was looking forward to taking note of ways the event would be different. It had been almost three years since my last attendance, so I was super excited. I was looking for a relaxed experience reconnecting with old friends, making new ones, and seeing what the world's finest menswear brands had to offer for the upcoming season. 

This season's experience was precisely that. I discovered new parts of Florence; I met with various brands to discuss the innovative ways they are pushing modern-day dressing for the modern man. I also created unforgettable memories with long laughs and conversations over lunches and dinners. 

There's more to talk about, but long story short, I can't wait until next season.

In the past, styling for me at #PittiUomo was always about the suits. It's the tailoring convention, so that should be no surprise. 

As the years have gone by, what I have enjoyed consuming from Pitti's attendance and presentation has been the inclusion of casualwear and knitwear with fine details. You can reference this in street-style round-ups and presentation lookbooks from many brands participating in the show. 

Styling for attendance this time, I wanted to experiment with what this liking would look like for me on the ground. I consulted my friend and stylist, Fred Kim, who worked with me in styling this look. We did not want to do anything too dressy - just something easy to put together, and that also felt good for someone who would be on their feet for most of the day.

I'm currently in a very minimal era with my style. This look exemplifies that. 

Creative Direction, @igeeokafor.
Photographed by @maieutcya.
Stylist, @_fredkim.

Diving into the world of fragrances this Father’s Day with a gift that encapsulates strength and wisdom - @isseymiyakeparfums L’Eau D’Issey Pour Homme Vétiver. This scent, inspired by the profoundly aromatic Vétiver grass native to India, mirrors the qualities we admire in our fathers. What makes this scent unique? Its main ingredient – Vétiver. Known for its strong, earthy, and distinctly woody aroma, Vétiver has roots that grow deep into the earth, symbolizing resilience and grounding - traits we often associate with our fathers. Gifting this fragrance isn’t about giving a pleasant scent; it’s about capturing a moment, a memory, a lesson learned. Each spritz brings to life those valuable moments spent with Dad in the heart of nature - sharing stories, absorbing wisdom, and creating bonds. As you tour the factory floor and stroll through the vast grounds, you'll gain an exclusive glimpse into Bentley's sustainability initiatives, a testament to its unwavering commitment to responsible luxury.

But the experience doesn't end there. As dusk falls, an unforgettable evening awaits - an intimate private dinner within the very heart of the Bentley factory. The journey continues into the North Pennines and the Northumberland National Park, where untamed landscapes and unspoiled beauty unfold before the eyes. Earlier this week, I had the pleasure of hosting a delightful dinner in Knightsbridge, where @settelondon by @scarpettarestaurants made for the most memorable culinary experience at the Bvlgari Hotel.

The evening kicked off with a Crudo Tasting that teased our taste buds with its enticing flavors, setting the tone for the culinary experience ahead. Following that, the Ravioli Cacio e Pepe transported me to Italy with its simple yet divine taste. The Pastrami Rib Eye was a real treat, tender and flavorful, showcasing Sette London's culinary expertise. And, of course, the John Dory with clams added a delightful touch to the meal.

The menu paid homage to the newly launched New York Nights concept, blending a bit of Manhattan chicness into the London scene.

It was a special evening that marked the grand debut of @bondofficialusa on London's social scene, and @settelondon by @scarpettarestaurants at the Bulgari Hotel in Knightsbridge provided the perfect food and setting.

With a dram in hand, I raised a toast to the night ahead. Of course, it was The Macallan Double Cask 15 Years Old that stole the spotlight. Its rich, velvety essence danced across our palates, a testament to the craftsmanship that had gone into creating this masterpiece. It was a night where long standing friendships were rekindled, and new ones were born - a testament to the harmonious blend of tradition and innovation.

With every sip, the whisky whispered notes of vanilla, toffee, and fruit; a melodic serenade that underscored the profound connections being forged around the room.

Mexico City resonates with my passion for art and design, and when I visited, it took me on an immersive journey through centuries of creativity. Whether that is through wandering its neighborhoods, its culinary scene, or architectural landscape. I love the city’s ability to blend both the old and new fostering artistic talent in such a welcoming atmosphere, and one of the most exciting parts of my trip was being able to share my new discoveries with my friend, @serenagoh.
 
I checked into @RitzCarltonMexicoCity for its luxury design, hospitality, and proximity to Mexico City’s most signature museums, restaurants, and street art. Visiting the Chapultepec Castle atop Chapultepec Hill was a gem of an experience. Our knowledgeable tour guide, a walking encyclopedia, brought the castle’s history to life, illuminating the castle’s many secrets and transforming it into a living, breathing testament to the nation’s past. My experience was nothing short of outstanding, and I cannot wait to return.
 
With its amazing travel benefits, my @MarriottBonvoy Brilliant® @AmericanExpress Card makes my trip to Mexico City to explore my love for art and design even better.

Finding that perfect holiday fragrance is a tradition I look forward to every year. I’ve discovered mine in @Penhaligons Halfeti, and I’m thrilled to share it with you. 

Available at @NeimanMarcus, Halfeti is more than just a scent; it’s a cocktail of everything I love about a signature fragrance. The opening notes of zesty grapefruit and sparkling bergamot remind me of holiday mornings full of excitement and joy. As the day unfolds, so does the scent, revealing a heart of exotic spices and the velvety touch of rose – a nod to those warm, festive evenings spent with loved ones. And when the night dawns, the rich blend of leather and oud in the base notes lingers like those cherished holiday memories. Each spritz of Halfeti is a celebration, an ideal companion for this season’s festivities. If you’re looking for a scent that’s as unique as your holiday moments, give Penhaligon’s Halfeti a try at Neiman Marcus. #Penhaligons

#RosewoodHotels Checked into Lagoon paradise @rwmayakoba this week. It’s not every day you enjoy the tranquil beauty of the lagoon intertwining with the utmost luxury of a five-star resort.

Here’s a bit of a room tour. There’s a lot to love. It’s contemporary design, local craftsmanship, its homage to Mayan culture and its comfort. Feels like my very own custom sanctuary. #RosewoodMayakoba

I had the incredible opportunity to visit @rwmayakoba just in time for the new year, and let me tell you, it was an experience like no other. The resort’s Curative Fire & Ice Therapy draws inspiration from ancient Mayan medicine, using a combination of warm and cool stones to relax muscles and provide an unparalleled sense of tranquility. The stone therapy, paired with a rejuvenating massage, not only enhances circulation and reduces muscular tension but also leaves you feeling rejuvenated and invigorated.

But that’s not all—Rosewood Mayakoba goes a step further by incorporating a traditional Mayan Sweat Lodge into various treatments. The resort even offers a cold plunge experience that you can pair with other treatments for a truly holistic wellness journey. It’s a place where ancient wisdom meets modern luxury, and it’s an experience I’ll never forget @rosewoodhotels. #RosewoodHotels #RosewoodMayakoba
